==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poultice
<hw>Poul"tice</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>puls</ets>,
pl. <ets>pultes</ets>, a thick pap; akin to Gr. <grk>po`ltos</grk>. Cf.
<er>Pulse</er> seeds.]</ety> <def>A soft composition, as of bread, bran,
or a mucilaginous substance, to be applied to sores, inflamed parts of
the body, etc.; a cataplasm.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Poultice</xex> relaxeth
the pores.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poultice</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Poultice
<hw>Poul"tice</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Poulticed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Poulticing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To apply a
poultice to; to dress with a poultice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poultive</ent>⟦br⟧
